    {"[head=1]Dusk Enclave[/head]"}

    {"[italic]\"We are not shadows cast by the light. We are penumbra, the dusk -- the space between day and night where both exist together.\"[/italic]"}

    The Dusk Enclave is a collective of extraplanars and interdimensional wanderers — those who have crossed the membrane between worlds and carry that crossing in their being. It is not a species, a religion, or an institution. It is a common ground built by those who understand that the universe is far larger than Lightspace admits, and that the people shaped by those wider spaces deserve recognition, dignity, and each other.

    The Enclave welcomes any entity who aligns with its values regardless of origin, plane, or nature. Membership demands genuine commitment: respect for the diversity of extradimensional experience, curiosity over dogma, and care for those who share the particular strangeness of existing between worlds.

    {"[head=2]Our foundations[/head]"}
    {"[head=3]Culture[/head]"}
    Honoring the full breadth of extradimensional cultures, traditions, and ways of knowing. No single plane, people, or cosmology holds the whole truth. The Enclave preserves and shares these traditions not as relics but as living knowledge — fostering exchange between members whose origins may be radically unlike one another.

    {"[head=3]Knowledge[/head]"}
    Inquiry into the mechanics of dimensional travel, planar physics, and the phenomena that Lightspace science struggles to categorize. Mapping thin places, studying phase anomalies, documenting the biological and cognitive effects of extradimensional existence, and building a body of understanding that treats interdimensional science as a serious discipline.

    {"[head=3]Advocacy[/head]"}
    Political and legal engagement on behalf of extradimensional entities and cryptid sophonts who lack formal recognition, rights, or protections. The Enclave works on that through coalition-building, documentation, and persistent pressure on institutions that would rather not acknowledge what they cannot categorize.

    {"[head=3]Community[/head]"}
    A distributed support network woven through existing societal structures. Sympathetic doctors, lawyers, engineers, bartenders, and officials. Safe spaces, shared information, and quiet assistance wherever members find themselves. The Enclave does not ask its members to be alone in strange places — it asks them to leave a light on for the next one through.
